<h1> Monday, August 28th </h1>
<h2> Learning Goals:<h2>
<h4> SWBAT:<h4>
<ul>
  <li>STRINGS ‐ explain what a string is and why it's used</li>
  <li>STRINGS ‐ create strings using double quotes</li>
  <li>STRINGS concatenate two strings using the + </li>
  <li>STRINGS ‐ use common string methods</li>
  <li>PUTS ‐ Explain what putsing is and what it's used for</li>
  <li>INT ‐ explain what an integer is and why it's used</li>
  <li>INT ‐ use common mathematical operations with integers</li>
  <li>INT ‐ understand that ruby rounds down when doing math with integers</li>
  <li>INT ‐ use typical methods like to_f and to_s to mutate integers</li>
  <li>FLT ‐ explain what a float is and why it's used</li>
  <li>FLT ‐ understand that math with floats produces floats and math with integers produces integers</li>
  <li>FLT ‐ use typical methods like to_i and to_s to mutate float</li>
  <li>FLT ‐ use common mathematical operations on floats</li>
  <li>STRINGS/VARIABLES ‐ interpolate a variable or a method within a string</li>
  <li>VAR ‐ use a variable in place of a piece of data</li>
  <li>VAR ‐ assign integers to variables</li>
  <li>VAR ‐ assign floats to variables</li>
  <li>VAR ‐ reassign the value of a variable</li>
</ul>

